http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Chief-Minister-to-launch-special-package-for-Ballari-tomorrow/article14000534.ece

Chief Minister Siddaramaiah will launch special schemes for the overall development of the district, announced during the byelection to Ballari (Rural) Assembly constituency in 2014, at a public meeting on Saturday at 11.30 a.m.Construction of residential schools, hostels for Scheduled Castes, Scheduled Tribes, backward classes and minorities, distribution of loans to self-help groups, drilling of borewells under the Ganga Kalyan scheme are some of them.H. Anjaneya, Minister of Social Welfare, and P.T. Parameshwar Naik, Minister of State for Labour and district incharge, on Thursday reviewed the arrangements being made by the officials for the programme.Briefing press persons, Mr. Anjaneya said that as promised earlier, his department had approved proposals for construction of residential schools, hostels, school buildings, and implementation of the Ganga Kalyan scheme, estimated to cost Rs. 325 crore.“We are implementing what had been promised. There has been some delay and I apologise for it,” he said.Mr. Parameshwar said that each of the 10,000 woman members of SHGs would be granted between Rs. 15,000 and Rs. 10,000 as subsidy and Rs. 5,000 in the form of loan.Mr. Naik said that Chief Minister would set in motion development works of other departments too and distribute cheques under various welfare schemes.They said that the Deputy Commissioner Sameer Shukla had been instructed to convene a meeting of bankers with regard to the loan component to the SHG members.The Ministers, along with legislators K.C. Kondaiah, N.Y. Gopalkrishna, and Anil Lad, and senior officials visited the municipal school grounds, the venue of the public meeting, to over see the preparations.